# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CONSTRUDATA-360 — Environment Variables Template
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env.local for local development:
#   cp .env.example .env.local
#
# For production (Vercel), set these variables in the Vercel Dashboard:
#   Settings → Environment Variables
#
# NEVER commit .env, .env.local, or any file with real credentials.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ─── Supabase ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Get these from your Supabase project: Settings → API
# Both VITE_* vars are SAFE to expose in the browser bundle:
#   - URL is your project hostname
#   - anon key is a public JWT scoped by Row-Level Security policies
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_anon_public_key_here

# Supabase Edge Function parse-rdo-sabesp
# Configure as a Supabase secret, not as VITE_*:
#   supabase secrets set LOVABLE_API_KEY=...
LOVABLE_API_KEY=your_lovable_gateway_key_here

# ⚠️ DO NOT add SERVICE_ROLE_KEY or DB_PASSWORD here with the VITE_ prefix.
# Anything starting with VITE_ is bundled into the browser. Service-role keys
# bypass RLS and must NEVER reach the client. Use them only in:
#   - Node scripts (without VITE_ prefix)
#   - GitHub Actions secrets
#   - Server-side functions
# Example (Node-only, never imported by Vite):
#   SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=...
#   SUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD=...

# ─── Web3Forms (landing contact form) ────────────────────────────────────────
# Get your key at: https://web3forms.com
VITE_WEB3FORMS_KEY=your_web3forms_access_key_here

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NOTE: Autodesk APS (Forge) credentials are NOT configured here.
# They are entered by the user at runtime via the BIM module settings modal
# and stored only in the browser's localStorage — never in code or .env files.
# For production use, consider implementing a backend proxy to avoid exposing
# the APS Client Secret in the browser.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
